Final Closed Review Summary
Done:
- Extended `RuntimePolicy` through IPC registration, companion route dispatch, plugin runtime boundaries, and subagent launch/run metadata.
- Persisted strict/normal/wide subagent policy profiles and grants through request/status/database metadata and delegated execution context.
- Moved persisted plugin auto-enable out of the bootstrap fast path while preserving default PluginManager behavior for existing callers.
- Added named network-policy helpers and moved embedding, Ollama, A2A, and startup diagnostic calls behind them.
- Migrated remaining secret-like settings into credential storage, tightened generic settings IPC with an allowlist, and routed connector secret config through credentials.
- Made companion artifact tickets one-time use.
- Split plugin managed-process ownership into `plugin-process-service` and validated plugin `runtimePermissions`.
- Split plugin discovery, persistent state, module loading/cache cleanup, and public summaries out of `PluginManager`; plugin entrypoints are now contained to their own plugin directory.
- Added explicit companion bearer-token expiry/rotation: authenticate rotates bearer credentials, validation rejects expired bearer tokens, and legacy bearer strings migrate into expiring credential records.
- Reduced custom-tool worker inherited environment and kept custom tools unsafe/brokered by default.
- Closed a remaining renderer raw IPC call path and expanded the Electron bridge hardening contract.

Next steps:
- None in this file. Start a fresh review from current code when another review pass is needed.
